Goodbye 2022, you are the year that shattered my heart, shattered my dreams. The challenge you put me through has been the hardest of my life. A year ago today my life changed completely and I had not seen it coming. The life I thought I had took a hard turn. I had to make decisions that were bigger than me, I had to make decisions for my children… With a broken heart and a shattered spirit I’ve been working through this year of pain while I raise my two kids to be compassionate, caring, and conscious beings. I will welcome the new year, and remember today and this very night one year ago when i felt my world fall apart but forced me to be strong through the birth of my son.
I’m working through the parts of me that fell in love with a fantasy.  Facing challenge head on, I had no choice, but to break through, not break down. I gave birth to my son in the midst of the storm of my life, my children give me every reason to go on every day… I wish to spend this journey growing into the best version of myself, so that I can raise children with a value system that is conscious.  I hope to one day tell them how much they taught me as I was trying to teach them. 

I wish for 2023 to heal our hearts, encourage women to support one another and be the change we want to see in the world! 

#happynewyear #heartout #goodbye2022 #goodbye

Another happy birthday to me! ❤️
I feel blessed to celebrate another birthday in this country and on Independence Day - I’m living the American dream, raising my two children in the country I could only have dreamed of being a part of. 
My birthday wish is to see this country thrive the way I always looked up to it as a little girl. That my kids will experience their own American dream… that I will continue, no matter what, to grow from adversity and move toward the light. I wish to take from my past the lessons learned and strengthen the values I honor and to pass them on to my kids. To never take a day for granted, to thrive in my independence as a woman and a mother, choose joy and inspire women to believe that it’s never too late to stand for what you believe in. That all the love we need is inside of us. 
#happybirthday #happybirthdaytome #4thofjulybaby #bornonthe4thofjuly #4thofjuly

Having beautiful bubblegum pink hair for a year, then stripping them down to blonde, then pregnancy and childbirth, then stress of personal life crisis, all destroyed my hair. My hair broke at the point where I stripped pink down and I colored my hair to natural brunette again. I came for help to trichologist and hair reconstruction expert @anna_astarte. I just had first hair restoration treatment done with her, and there is a positive improvement in my hair structure. I need to restore the damaged hair, I cut lots of it off and working on the regrowth. I’m planning to do more treatments with @anna_astarte. Thank you for helping me in the process to restore my hair to long and beautiful some day! Wish me luck guys! 
#hair #hairhealth #hairrestoration #trichology #hairexpert
